    <h2>Learn to Introduce Yourself</h2>
    <p>In this unit, you will learn how to introduce yourself and others in English. This is a very important skill, as it helps you to communicate with people you meet for the first time. Let's explore some key vocabulary and expressions for greetings and introductions!</p>

    <h3>Key Vocabulary</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Hello</strong> - A common greeting.</li>
      <li><strong>Good morning</strong> - Used to greet someone in the morning.</li>
      <li><strong>Good afternoon</strong> - Used in the afternoon.</li>
      <li><strong>Good evening</strong> - Used when you meet someone in the evening.</li>
      <li><strong>How are you?</strong> - A way to ask someone about their well-being.</li>
      <li><strong>Nice to meet you</strong> - A polite way to express pleasure when meeting someone for the first time.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Common Expressions for Introductions</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>My name is...</strong> - Used to introduce yourself.</li>
      <li><strong>What’s your name?</strong> - A way to ask someone’s name.</li>
      <li><strong>I’m from...</strong> - Used to say where you are from.</li>
      <li><strong>Where are you from?</strong> - A way to ask someone about their origin.</li>
      <li><strong>I’m a student.</strong> - You can use this to tell someone your occupation or role.</li>
      <li><strong>How old are you?</strong> - A question to ask someone's age.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Grammar Focus</h3>
    <p>In this unit, we will focus on the verb <strong>to be</strong> in the present simple tense. The verb "to be" is used to describe people, places, and things. Here are some examples:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>I am</strong> a student. (affirmative)</li>
      <li><strong>You are</strong> my friend. (affirmative)</li>
      <li><strong>He/She is</strong> a teacher. (affirmative)</li>
      <li><strong>Are you</strong> from Spain? (question)</li>
      <li><strong>Yes, I am</strong>. (positive response)</li>
      <li><strong>No, I am not</strong>. (negative response)</li>
    </ul>

